Golovnin gave out the land left to him after the allotment of the peasants, not for profit, but to tie them to the village and the economy. a school for boys, later transferred to a special stone building, with apartments for two teachers; at the school - a physics office, a meteorological station, two libraries: one of them (5000 volumes) was available to the surrounding population. Golovnin was constantly interested in the progress of the school, was in correspondence with its teachers, and annually provided financial and other assistance. In 1870 he an elementary school for girls was also founded, in a special wooden house. They also opened a hospital in Gulynki, with a maternity shelter.